I was going to give ZPizza 4 stars then I started thinking....why not 5? I have never had a problem with service, staff is always friendly, pizza is always good with little inconsistency, they now have the killer of all Vegan cheeses.....Daiya so why not? Well, 5 stars is reserved for someplace or thing that you cannot live without. If it were to go away, or you were never able to have it again, then your life would somehow always be one notch below what it could be.  I am not sure I feel THAT strongly about ZPizza, but then I realized if I gave it 4 stars I would be the first non-5star review for this location! I can't bring that kind of Karma on myself! 5 stars it is!!  The Soy Berkley Veggie pizza is really all I ever get, it's a great pie for sure. I like mine with wheat crust and lightly baked and most of the time Zpizza does just that. The buy one get one free Tuesday deal is something we hit frequently, I understand that it's going away and will be replaced with another customer appreciation deal but really, I am surprised it has made it this long. It was quite the deal.   The Soy cheese used to contain Casein which doesn't exactly make it vegan friendly. Most all stores now have switched to Daiya vegan cheese(which isn't soy but actually made from a root). It's the tits(see what I did there? Tits is a hot new word for describing something top notch, but tits is also what dairy cheese come from, this cheese doesn't; so you can stop thinking about a cows tits and where your dairy cheese comes from, clever I know) The cheese is fantastic, Whole Foods carries it for there pizzas too.   I have had there yuppie veggie sandwich before as well ( I was really hungry and had a pizza and sandwich if you must know) and it too is good. The pizza at Zpizza might not impress pizza snobs looking for authentic Sicilian, Brooklyn, etc pizza but the pizza is good and creative and uses better ingredients then most places, therefore actually making it somewhat good for you(ok, it's still pizza but I am trying here).  I haven't been to ZPizza in a few weeks and after checking there menu it looks like they have made a few changes, my Soy Berkley pizza now has a new name and new ingredients. I see some other changes as well, change is good, I am not mad(NOOOO!!!!). Time to see what new pizza creation I can put together, the addition of new and healthy ingredients can only help.

